# WordPress Plugin Safety Patterns

> **Critical patterns learned from production incidents**
> Last updated: 2026-02-21

---

## ❌ ЗАПРЕЩЁННЫЕ ПАТТЕРНЫ

### 1. CSS/JS Optimization Plugins — NO Auto-Installation

**Affected plugins:**
- Asset Cleanup / Asset CleanUp Pro
- Autoptimize
- WP Rocket
- W3 Total Cache
- Fast Velocity Minify
- Any plugin with "optimize", "minify", "combine" in description

**Problem:**
Even with DEFAULT settings, these plugins can block critical CSS/JS files, causing complete visual breakdown.

**Symptoms:**
- Site returns HTTP 200
- HTML content present
- **CSS not loaded** — page displays as plain HTML
- JavaScript errors in console
- Elementor layouts broken

**Why it happens:**
- Aggressive default rules block "unnecessary" assets
- Conflict with existing cache layers (Seraphinite Accelerator)
- Regex patterns catch legitimate files
- Load order dependencies broken by combination

**Example incident (2026-02-21):**
```
Before: 383KB page with CSS
After Asset Cleanup activation: 162KB plain HTML (CSS blocked)
Stylesheets: 1 → 25 after deactivation
```

**✅ CORRECT approach:**
1. Measure baseline (PageSpeed score BEFORE changes)
2. Install plugin
3. **IMMEDIATELY check site visually** (open in browser)
4. Configure ONLY via WordPress Admin UI (never WP-CLI)
5. Enable Test Mode first
6. Test after EACH setting change
7. Monitor for 24 hours before declaring success

---

### 2. Plugin Configuration via WP-CLI — NEVER

**Problem:**
Using `wp eval` + `update_option()` to configure plugins causes type mismatches.

**Example:**
```bash
# ❌ WRONG
wp eval 'update_option("plugin_settings", ["key" => "value"]);'

# Plugin expects JSON string, receives PHP array
# Result: Fatal error: json_decode(): Argument #1 ($json) must be of type string
```

**✅ CORRECT methods:**
1. WordPress Admin UI (always safe)
2. Plugin's documented WP-CLI commands (if exists)
3. Default settings (safest)

**Incident reference:** Asset Cleanup crash (2026-02-21)
- Settings saved as PHP array instead of JSON string
- Site Fatal Error on every page load
- Downtime: 5 minutes

---

### 3. Global CSS Overrides via mu-plugin — BE CAREFUL

**Problem:**
Broad CSS selectors affect unintended elements.

**Example:**
```php
// ❌ BAD: Affects ALL elements with this class
add_action('wp_head', function() {
    echo '<style>
        span.elementor-heading-title {
            color: #ffffff !important;
        }
    </style>';
});
```

**What breaks:**
- White text on white backgrounds (light sections)
- New accessibility issues (contrast violations)
- Overrides intentional design choices

**✅ CORRECT approach:**
1. Use Elementor → Edit Widget → Style tab directly
2. Add class to specific widget: `.my-dark-hero h2 { color: #fff; }`
3. Use `!important` ONLY when absolutely necessary
4. Test on ALL page sections (dark + light backgrounds)

---

## ✅ ПРАВИЛЬНЫЕ ПАТТЕРНЫ

### Safe Plugin Installation Workflow

```bash
# 1. Baseline measurement
# Run PageSpeed Insights, note scores

# 2. Install plugin
wp plugin install PLUGIN_SLUG --allow-root

# 3. STOP — DO NOT activate yet
# Read plugin documentation first

# 4. Activate
wp plugin activate PLUGIN_SLUG --allow-root

# 5. IMMEDIATE visual check
curl -s "https://site.com/" | grep -c "stylesheet"
# Should return >5 for typical WordPress site

# 6. Open in browser
# Check homepage, key pages, Elementor sections

# 7. Configure via Admin UI ONLY
# Enable Test Mode if available
# Make ONE change at a time
# Check site after each change

# 8. Monitor
# Check error logs: wp-content/debug.log
# Monitor for 24 hours
# Run PageSpeed again

# 9. If anything breaks
wp plugin deactivate PLUGIN_SLUG --allow-root
find ~/path/cache/ -type f -delete
curl "https://site.com/wp-json/sk/v1/full-clear"
```

---

### Recovery Procedure (Site Broken After Plugin)

```bash
# 1. Identify suspect plugins
wp plugin list --allow-root | grep -E "optim|minif|cache|speed"

# 2. Deactivate suspect plugin
wp plugin deactivate PLUGIN_SLUG --allow-root

# 3. Clear ALL caches
curl "https://site.com/wp-json/sk/v1/full-clear" -u admin:pass
find ~/cache/ -type f -delete

# 4. Verify restoration
curl -s "https://site.com/" | grep -c "stylesheet"
# Should be >5

# 5. Check site visually
# Open in browser, verify CSS loads

# 6. Clean up
wp option delete plugin_settings_option_name --allow-root
wp plugin uninstall PLUGIN_SLUG --allow-root

# 7. Document incident
# Create post-mortem in logs/self-learning/
```

---

### CSS Fixes Best Practices

**For accessibility contrast issues:**

1. **Identify exact element:**
   ```bash
   # Use browser DevTools → Inspect Element
   # Note full selector chain
   ```

2. **Fix in Elementor directly:**
   - Edit widget → Style tab → Typography/Color
   - Widget-specific, no side effects

3. **If must use CSS:**
   ```php
   // ✅ GOOD: Specific selector
   add_action('wp_head', function() {
       echo '<style id="my-specific-fix">
           .hero-section .elementor-heading-title {
               color: #ffffff !important;
               text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
           }
       </style>';
   }, 999);
   ```

4. **Test on multiple sections:**
   - Hero (dark background)
   - Content (light background)
   - Footer (dark background)
   - Mobile view

---

## Detection Rules

### When to be EXTRA careful:

**Plugin name contains:**
- "optim", "minif", "cache", "speed", "boost", "performance"
- "asset", "cleanup", "compress", "combine"

**Plugin description mentions:**
- "minify CSS/JS"
- "combine files"
- "defer scripts"
- "remove unused CSS"
- "critical CSS"

**High-risk scenarios:**
1. Site already has cache plugin (Seraphinite, WP Rocket)
2. Using page builder (Elementor, Divi)
3. Heavy use of custom CSS
4. Many third-party scripts (analytics, chat, etc.)

### Green flags (safer plugins):

- Read-only (Site Kit, MonsterInsights)
- Content-only (Yoast, RankMath)
- Well-documented WP-CLI commands
- "Test Mode" feature available
- 100K+ active installs + 4.5+ rating
- Official repository, regular updates

---

## Metrics to Track

**Before ANY optimization plugin:**

| Metric | Tool | Baseline |
|--------|------|----------|
| PageSpeed Performance | pagespeed.web.dev | Note score |
| PageSpeed Accessibility | pagespeed.web.dev | Note score |
| Load time | curl -w "%{time_total}" | Note seconds |
| Page size | curl -w "%{size_download}" | Note bytes |
| CSS files loaded | grep -c stylesheet | Note count |
| JavaScript files | grep -c "<script" | Note count |

**After plugin activation:**
- Re-run ALL metrics
- Compare to baseline
- If ANY metric degrades significantly → investigate
- If visual breakage → immediate rollback

